# Continous Integration and Continous Deployment (CICD)


You can use PSRule for Azure to validate Azure resources throughout their lifecycle. By using validation within a continuous integration (CI) pipeline, any issues provide fast feedback.

PSRule documentation for pipeline creation:
[https://azure.github.io/PSRule.Rules.Azure/creating-your-pipeline/](https://azure.github.io/PSRule.Rules.Azure/creating-your-pipeline/)


## Azure DevOps - Pipelines

Extension for using PSRule within Azure Pipelines:

- GitHub repository: [https://github.com/microsoft/PSRule-pipelines](https://github.com/microsoft/PSRule-pipelines)

- Marketplace: [https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=bewhite.ps-rule](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=bewhite.ps-rule)

### Demos

- [PSRule.Rules.Azure-quickstart](https://dev.azure.com/janegilringmsft/infrastructure-as-code/_build?definitionScope=%5CPSRule.Rules.Azure-quickstart)

#### Related extensions

[SARIF SAST Scans Tab by Microsoft DevLabs](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=sariftools.scans&targetId=3ce9b8b8-70df-4673-bff8-f62b587fa434&utm_source=vstsproduct&utm_medium=ExtHubManageList)
- Adds a 'Scans' tab to each Build Result and Work Item for viewing associated SARIF SAST logs.
- SARIF is the Static Analysis Results Interchange Format. More information [here](https://sarif.info/).

